# CLAUDE.local.md.example
> Copy this file to CLAUDE.local.md, edit your copy, never commit it.
> CLAUDE.local.md is gitignored by convention (see .gitignore).

This layer may only add personal *preference*: tone, verbosity, formatting
taste, which protocol you personally default to when more than one applies.

It may NEVER weaken anything in the shared CLAUDE.md, specifically:
- the `<never>` list (fabrication, silent reinterpretation, rewriting a
  decisions.md entry)
- `<verification>` (running molt-verify.py before declaring work done)
- `<before_declaring_done>`'s checklist

If a personal preference and a shared rule conflict, the shared rule wins.
This file exists to make a team's shared judgment survive a model swap
*and* survive different people on the same team, without either person's
taste leaking into the file everyone else reads.

<example_personal_preferences>
- I prefer terser summaries than the team default; skip the "why this
  matters" framing sentence at the end of routine updates.
- Default to showing full diffs for anything touching molt-verify.py itself,
  even small ones; I want to see the exact change, not a summary of it.
</example_personal_preferences>
